# Experiment Mode Protocol

Experiment (experiment mode) runs prepared code to produce results **and records them back into the docs** -- ingestion is the closing step of this mode, not a separate one. It is a mutating, compute-bearing Claude Code mode. Writing the source it runs is Implement mode (`docs/operations/implement-mode.md`).

## 1. Trigger

"Run it", "train / evaluate", "record the result", "ingest this result file".

## 2. Run Discipline

Do not change source during a run (that is a separate Implement task). Write outputs to a **new** directory distinct from prior {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} outputs; never overwrite existing results. Judge each locked success criterion (from `docs/project/project-status.md`) mechanically against its threshold.

## 3. The Prompt

Build the run prompt from the **Experiment skeleton in `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md` section 4.2**, or the Result-Ingestion skeleton (section 4.4) when a result lands without a fresh run. Task artifacts go under `${CLAUDE_DIR}/{TASK_ID}/`; default label `EXPERIMENT` (see `docs/operations/directory-map.md` section 4).

## 4. Closing Step: Record

Recording is mandatory and is what makes Experiment distinct from "just running": numbers to `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`; verdict + next task to `docs/project/project-status.md`; a row to `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md` and a body to `docs/project/themes/theme-bodies.md`; lever state to `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md`. Then run `make docs-check`.

## 5. Forbidden

- Editing source mid-run.
- Overwriting prior results or checkpoints.
- Presenting a cross-tier comparison as final evidence, or a test-label oracle as deployable performance.
